profile_positions.description:
Leading core strategic horizon of Philips Experience Design:
• Designing and implementing training program for our Design community (and beyond);
• Operationalising our core horizon by co-creating with global, multi-disciplinary teams of different businesses;
• Continuous improvement check by establishing Design KPIs, measuring progress and evidence-based action (within a change-management framework)
• Promoting synergies across different design domains (digital, product, service, communication design) towards achieving our strategic goals 
• Supporting technologies such as AR/VR, Artificial Intelligence to integrate the Philips Design Language System

• Actively collaborated in establishing and structuring a team of 15 Designers for the Philips EMR Business;
• Established the Design Principles, UX Patterns and Heuristics for the Philips EMR Business, that paved the migration process of more than 700 applications towards UX consistency, improved usability and the Philips Design Language;
• Created best practices for optimising and leaning up UX Patterns, balancing user, context and tech requirements;
• Co-created, prototyped, tested and transferred innovations in partnership with Philips Research to the Philips EMR

Development and collaboration in several research projects entailing 
1) entertainment/educational games for children through physical objected with embedded technology (Fiducial markers); 
2) Evaluation of Mobile Applications in Virtual Environments; 
3) Combining EEG and EyeGaze Interaction data in a visualization project.
